Privacy Policy for TopLearners JAMB CBT Practice App

1. Introduction:
   - Welcome to the JAMB CBT Practice App's Privacy Policy. This document outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information in connection with the app.

2. Information Collection:
   - We collect information during registration, including name, email, and location. User interactions within the app, such as performance and progress metrics, are also gathered.

3. Use of Personal Information:
   - Your personal information enhances your learning experience, tracks progress, and tailors app features to your preferences. We do not share or sell your data to third parties.

4. Data Security:
   - Robust security measures, including encryption protocols and secure storage practices, safeguard your data from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.

5. Cookies and Similar Technologies:
   - Cookies and similar technologies are used to improve app functionality, analyze usage patterns, and personalize content. Manage your cookie preferences within the app settings.

6. Third-Party Integrations:
   - The app may integrate third-party services for analytics or app improvement. Users are encouraged to review the privacy policies of these services.

7. In-App Communications:
   - Notifications, updates, or relevant information may be sent through the app. Control communication preferences in the app settings.

8. Children's Privacy:
   - The app is not intended for users under 13. If personal information from children is identified, it is promptly deleted.

9. User Control:
   - You have the right to access, modify, or delete personal information. Contact our support team for assistance with data-related requests.

10. Retention of Data:
   - Personal information is retained only for the duration necessary to fulfill outlined purposes. Request data deletion after discontinuing app usage.

11. Data Sharing:
    - Personal information is not shared with external parties except where necessary for app functionality or required by law. We ensure third parties adhere to strict data protection standards.

12. User Feedback and Surveys:
    - Feedback through surveys may be collected to improve app features. Participation is voluntary, and survey responses are anonymized unless explicit consent for disclosure is obtained.

13. Offline Data:
    - The app may store certain data locally on your device for offline use. This data is subject to the same security measures as online data and is solely used for enhancing your offline learning experience.

14. Analytics and Aggregated Data:
    - User interactions are analyzed to improve the app's overall performance. Aggregated data, devoid of personally identifiable information, may be shared for research or statistical purposes.

15. Notification Preferences:
    - Customize notification preferences within the app, allowing control over the frequency and type of communications received.

16. Accessibility and User Support:
    - We are committed to ensuring accessibility for all users. Contact our support team for assistance or accommodations due to accessibility concerns.

17. Governing Law:
    - This Privacy Policy is governed by and construed in accordance with the laws. Any disputes arising under or in connection with this policy are subject to the exclusive jurisdiction.

By continuing to use the TopLearners JAMB CBT Practice App, you agree to the expanded terms outlined in this privacy policy. For inquiries or concerns regarding privacy matters, contact our designated privacy officer at [jambcbtguru@email.com]. Last updated: 9th January 2024.
